<!DOCTYPE html>
<title>Test control of preserve of whitespaces by xml:space attribute, and serialization of the attribute for foreign elements</title><p>
      Welcome to this example.
      Whitespaces are <span> preserved </span> due to use of xml:space='preserve'.
      <br>
      <span>However, this can be reverted to default when necessary.</span>
    </p><math xml:space=preserve>
      <mrow>
        <malignmark/>
        <mtext xml:space=default>This is text</mtext>
      </mrow>
    </math>
